To start a heroku app
see the package json file and delete the lock json file 
see that there are no duplications present and engines should contain both node and npm if there is duplicacy delete that one
open git repo redirect to the place where you are running the folder from
Go to the official site of heroku 
give the app name of your choice
after setting the name of the app direct you view towards finding heroku cli and open the heroku cli dialogue box and see the steps
follow the steps it should launch your git repo
-------------**----------------
after making changes in js files
type heroku open 
check git status
then add the files with git add .
then commit changes
then launch in cmd : heroku login
git push heroku master
it should open your browser with new refreshed data
